<h1>Installing libcouchbase C Library Mac OS X</h1>
<p class="lead">The libcouchbase C library is the actual communication layer for the Couchbase gem. It is a binary protocol based "Smart Client" that maintains a map of the Couchbase cluster topology to reduce latency (increases speed). Although Couchbase can be used with a memcached client (like the Dalli gem), the Couchbase SDK's perform much much faster!</p>

<span class="badge badge-info">Tip !</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;The best way to ensure a smooth installation is to upgrade everything to latest versions before installing!<br />
<span class="badge badge-info">Tip !</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;If you upgraded to Mountain Lion here's a nice guide/tips by Thoughtbot to setup command line: <a href="http://robots.thoughtbot.com/post/27985816073/the-hitchhikers-guide-to-riding-a-mountain-lion" target="_blank">The Hitchhikerâ€™s Guide to Riding a Mountain Lion</a>

